'''Interstate 476''' is a 130.5-mile long Interstate highway that travels between [[I-95]] near [[Chester, Pennsylvania]] and [[I-81]] near [[Scranton, Pennsylvania]]. Since its completion in [[1996]], I-476 has been the longest auxiliary [[interstate highway]] in the [[United States]].

The route consists of both the 20.5-mile '''Mid-County Expressway''' (locally referred to as the '''Blue Route''') through the [[Philadelphia]] suburbs, and the 110-mile '''Northeast Extension''' of the [[Pennsylvania Turnpike]] connecting the western Philadelphia area with the [[Lehigh Valley]], the [[Poconos]], and the [[Scranton, Pennsylvania|Scranton]]-[[Wilkes-Barre, Pennsylvania|Wilkes-Barre]] metropolitan area.

